properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 6 at 10:15AM PST until January 6 at 6:00PM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Snow continued above 4000 feet. Additional snow
accumulations of 4 to 8 inches.

* WHERE...Cascade mountains and valleys of Pierce and Lewis
Counties, including the Crystal Mountain Ski Area, Paradise on
Mount Rainier, Ashford, Randle, and Packwood.

* WHEN...Until 6 PM PST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The Northwest Avalanche Center expects high
avalanche danger to continue through Tuesday with dangerous
conditions through Wednesday. Check nwac.us for the latest
avalanche conditions.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

For the latest road conditions in Washington state, call 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 PM PST THIS EVENING ABOVE 4000 FEET... ...WINTER STORM WARNING HAS EXPIRED
